# Commit Message Template
# 
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature for users
#   fix      - Bug fix for users  
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style/formatting (no logic change)
#   refactor - Code restructuring (no behavior change)
#   test     - Test additions or modifications
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   ci       - CI/CD changes
#   build    - Build system changes
#
# Scope: Optional module/component name in parentheses
#
# Subject: Complete the sentence "This commit will..."
#   - Use imperative mood (add, not added/adds)
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Limit to 250 characters (recommended)
#
# Body: Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Use bullet points for multiple items
#   - Separate from subject with blank line
#
# Footer: References and breaking changes
#   - Fixes #123
#   - Closes #456
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: description
#
# Example:
# feat(auth): add OAuth2 integration for Google login
#
# - Implement OAuth2 flow with Google provider
# - Add token refresh mechanism  
# - Update user model with OAuth fields
# - Add integration tests
#
# This enables users to sign in with their Google accounts,
# reducing friction in the registration process.
#
# Closes #789

<TYPE>(<SCOPE>): <SUBJECT>

<BODY>

<FOOTER>